# switch: An Alternative to many elseif

When you need to compare the same variable against many different values, `switch` can be cleaner.

```php
switch ($variable) {
    case value1:
        // code
        break;
    case value2:
        // code
        break;
    default:
        // code if no match
}
```

```php
<?php
$day = "Monday";

switch ($day) {
    case "Monday":
        echo "Start of work week";
        break;
    case "Friday":
        echo "TGIF!";
        break;
    case "Saturday":
    case "Sunday":
        echo "Weekend!";
        break;
    default:
        echo "Midweek";
}
// Output: Start of work week
?>
```

Notice how multiple cases can share code by omitting `break`.

## Fallthrough

If you forget `break`, PHP will continue executing the next case's code, even if the condition doesn't match. This is called fallthrough.

Sometimes intentional (like for multiple values), but often a bug.

```php
// This will print both messages!
switch (1) {
    case 1:
        echo "One";
    case 2:
        echo "Two";
}
// Output: OneTwo
```

